h3. Problem Definition
JIRA mail handler stores value for _catchemail_ configuraion (and possibly other fields) without striping leading and trailing spaces. This lead to stranger misconfiguration problems like: 
{code:borderStyle=solid}
2016-04-27 23:38:38,419 INFO [JIRA] atlassian-scheduler-quartz1.clustered_Worker-2 anonymous   Mail Handler Service  Mail Handler Service[10210]: Cannot handle message as the recipient(s) (Jira@a.com, admin@a.com) do not match the catch email  Jira@a.com
{code}
Please note additional leading space in error. 

h3. Suggested Solution
Strip leading and trailing spaces

h3. Notes:
{code:borderStyle=solid}
jiradb64=# select * from propertystring WHERE ID='22502';
  id   |                                                                              propertyvalue
 22502 | project=PRG,issuetype=3,catchemail= Jira@a.com,bulk=ignore,createusers=false,notifyusers=false,ccwatcher=false,ccassignee=true,stripquotes=false
(1 row)
{code}

