h3. Problem Definition

Currently our Documentation provides the following guidance for upgrading JIRA and Supported plugins.  

{quote}
If you have installed JIRA plugins (i.e. not included with JIRA), verify that they will be compatible with the version of JIRA you are upgrading to. You can find a plugin's compatibility information from the plugin's home page on the Atlassian Plugin Exchange.
{quote}

h3. Suggested Solution

The Universal Plugin Manager is able to check Plugin versions against newer releases. This simpler approach should be taken for customers to check their compatibility when upgrading a running Instance. See: [Checking add-on compatibility with application updates|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/UPM/Checking+add-on+compatibility+with+application+updates] for more details. 

 
h3. Workaround
Follow the manual instructions for checking compatibility.

